This paper is about conversation modelling, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a new model for conversation modelling that focuses on learning essential concepts in the context and response. This involves unsupervised learning, which is a common theme in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model also involves training to learn response concepts, which is a task that falls under the category of deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of mutual information, which is a statistical measure commonly used in neural networks and reinforcement learning (cs.NE). Finally, the paper proposes a new model that achieves significant improvement over existing baselines, which is a common theme in systems and control (cs.SD).
